Okay if you where to try and compile this you would come up with an error because modIcon does not exsist in the client, you may be asking why? well because the object ModIcons is a background array NOT a sprite array so now we have to create a new Sprite array which i called "modIcon"

[code]public Sprite[] modIcon = new Sprite[2];[/code]



you can place that where ever you see fit. next we have to load the images into the array, to do this look for 

[code]          
  for(int l4 = 0; l4 < 2; l4++)
                modIcons[l4] = new Background(streamLoader_2, "mod_icons", l4);
[/code]


Replace that with:
[code]
            for(int l4 = 0; l4 < 2; l4++){ //adds bracket because we have more than 1 action happening
                modIcons[l4] = new Background(streamLoader_2, "mod_icons", l4); // original background array being filled
				modIcon[l4] = new Sprite(streamLoader_2, "mod_icons", l4); // our custom sprite array being filled
			} // close bracket
[/code]


now login and say something ingame and you will get this result:

